StatAvg Federated IDS under Non-IID Settings

A Federated Learning-based Intrusion Detection System (IDS) designed to handle non-IID (Non-Independent and Identically Distributed) data using StatAvg normalization techniques for improved model performance and stability across distributed clients.

📌 Project Overview

Traditional centralized intrusion detection systems require sharing sensitive network traffic data with a central server, leading to privacy and security concerns.

This project implements a Federated Learning IDS where multiple clients collaboratively train a global model without sharing raw data. To improve learning under non-IID environments, the project uses StatAvg normalization, which helps stabilize training across heterogeneous client distributions.

🚀 Features
Federated Learning based IDS
Handles Non-IID client data distribution
StatAvg normalization approach
Privacy-preserving training
Distributed client-server architecture
Machine Learning based attack detection
Performance evaluation metrics and visualizations
  
